review_text:
_Saw V_ was the worst of the series, and Jigsaw is basically just _Saw V_ again but worse. So, that's not exactly a glowing review. But that said: I was anticipating the worst for the ending, but the climax actually wound up being pretty satisfying, or at least, satisfying enough to give me the "Not good, but better than I was expecting" feeling by the time the credits rolled.

_Final rating:★★ - Had some things that appeal to me, but a poor finished product._
